# test_kwcov_variants.jl — pillar-1: keyword-ISOLATION coverage for NE/CS/LS vs live Fortran.
#
# Broadens NE/CS/LS toward SN's keyword-coverage breadth so "100% drop-in" is defensible per variant.
# Each scenario = the variant's canonical stand (net01/cst01/lst01 tree data) + ONE isolated keyword,
# validated BIT-EXACT against the freshly-relinked live binary (goldens in test/fixtures/kwcov/*.live.sum,
# generated by test/harness/{ne,cs,ls}_oracle.sh — NOT a stale committed golden).
#
# CRITICAL (memory: "run_keyfile probes need variant="): run_keyfile MUST be given the scenario's variant,
# else it defaults to SN (5-yr cycles, SN model) on NE/CS/LS data and fabricates gross divergence.
#
# Bit-exact scenarios are `==`; any non-ULP divergence is a documented `@test_broken` with a named reason.

using Test, FVSjl

const _KCV_DIR = joinpath(@__DIR__, "..", "fixtures", "kwcov")

